        "description": {
            "value": "<p>These thin cloth wraps, which are illegal to use in Highhelm's organized brawls, blend into the skin and add an edge to your blows. The wraps are <em>+1 striking @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Wounding] handwraps of mighty blows</em>. When you invest the wraps, they gain the effects of a 3rd-level <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Disguise Magic]{Magic Aura}</em> spell to appear non-magical and resemble simple bandages. Casual observers are unlikely to notice anything amiss with the wraps, but a creature that succeeds at a @Check[type:perception|dc:25] check can notice something is off about them, though they would still need to find other means to discern the magical nature of the wraps.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">R</span> envision</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per minute;</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> You cause a creature within reach to take bleed damage</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You use your foe's pain to reinvigorate you. You gain temporary Hit Points equal to the value of the triggering bleed damage, up to a maximum of 10 temporary HP. These temporary Hit Points remain for 1 minute.</p>"
